<Base title="Privacy Policy">
  <div>
    <h2>Customer privacy notice</h2>

    <p>
      This privacy notice tells you what to expect us to do with your personal
      information.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#contact" data-anchor="#contact">Contact details</a></li>
      <li>
        <a href="#collect" data-anchor="#collect"
          >What information we collect, use, and why</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#lawful" data-anchor="#lawful"
          >Lawful bases and data protection rights</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#infofrom" data-anchor="#infofrom"
          >Where we get personal information from</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#retention" data-anchor="#retention"
          >How long we keep information</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#share" data-anchor="#share">Who we share information with</a>
      </li>
      <li><a href="#complain" data-anchor="#complain">How to complain</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h2><a class="anchor" id="contact"></a>Contact details</h2>
    <h3>Email</h3>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:trustees@percymain.org">trustees@percymain.org</a>
    </p>
    <h2>
      <a class="anchor" id="collect"></a>What information we collect, use, and
      why
    </h2>

    <p>
      We collect or use the following information to <strong
        >receive donations or funding and organise fundraising activities</strong
      >:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Names and contact details</li>
      <li>Addresses</li>
      <li>Payment or banking details</li>
      <li>Donation history</li>
      <li>Health information</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      We collect or use the following personal information for <strong
        >service updates or marketing purposes</strong
      >:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Names and contact details</li>
      <li>Marketing preferences</li>
      <li>IP addresses</li>
      <li>Website and app user journey information</li>
    </ul>
    <div>
      <p>
        We collect or use the following personal information to <strong
          >comply with legal requirements</strong
        >:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Contact information</li>
        <li>Health and safety information</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We collect or use the following personal information for <strong
          >dealing with queries, complaints or claims</strong
        >:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Names and contact details</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>
        <a class="anchor" id="lawful"></a>Lawful bases and data protection
        rights
      </h2>
      <div>
        <p>
          Under UK data protection law, we must have a “lawful basis” for
          collecting and using your personal information. There is a list of
          possible lawful bases in the UK GDPR. You can find out more about
          lawful bases on the ICO’s website.
        </p>
        <p>
          Which lawful basis we rely on may affect your data protection rights
          which are in brief set out below. You can find out more about your
          data protection rights and the exemptions which may apply on the ICO’s
          website:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right of access</strong> - You have the right to ask us
            for copies of your personal information. You can request other information
            such as details about where we get personal information from and who
            we share personal information with. There are some exemptions which means
            you may not receive all the information you ask for. <a
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#roa"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              >You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right to rectification</strong> - You have the right to
            ask us to correct or delete personal information you think is inaccurate
            or incomplete.
            <a
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#rtr"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              >You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right to erasure</strong> - You have the right to ask us
            to delete your personal information. <a
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#rte"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              >You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right to restriction of processing</strong> - You have the
            right to ask us to limit how we can use your personal information. <a
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#rtrop"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              >You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right to object to processing</strong> - You have the right
            to object to the processing of your personal data. <a
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#rto"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              >You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right to data portability</strong> - You have the right
            to ask that we transfer the personal information you gave us to another
            organisation, or to you. <a
              rel="noopener"
              data-udi="umb://document/85f0330efe3c4504abdf2bf9e052ddc2"
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#rtdp"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              data-anchor="#rtdp">You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your right to withdraw consent</strong> – When we use consent
            as our lawful basis you have the right to withdraw your consent at any
            time.
            <a
              rel="noopener"
              data-udi="umb://document/85f0330efe3c4504abdf2bf9e052ddc2"
              href="/for-organisations/advice-for-small-organisations/create-your-own-privacy-notice/your-data-protection-rights/#rtwc"
              target="_blank"
              title="Your data protection rights"
              data-anchor="#rtwc">You can read more about this right here</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you make a request, we must respond to you without undue delay and
          in any event within one month.
        </p>
        <p>
          To make a data protection rights request, please contact us using the
          contact details at the top of this privacy notice.
        </p>
      </div>
      <h3>Our lawful bases for the collection and use of your data</h3>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div>
        <p>
          Our lawful bases for collecting or using personal information to <strong
            >receive donations or funding and organise fundraising activities</strong
          > are:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> - we have permission from you after we gave
            you all the relevant information. All of your data protection rights
            may apply, except the right to object. To be clear, you do have the right
            to withdraw your consent at any time.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal obligation</strong> - we have to collect or use your information
            so we can comply with the law. All of your data protection rights may
            apply, except the right to erasure, the right to object and the right
            to data portability.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Our lawful bases for collecting or using personal information for <strong
            >service updates or marketing purposes</strong
          > are:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> - we have permission from you after we gave
            you all the relevant information. All of your data protection rights
            may apply, except the right to object. To be clear, you do have the right
            to withdraw your consent at any time.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Our lawful bases for collecting or using personal information to <strong
            >comply with legal requirements</strong
          > are:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> - we have permission from you after we gave
            you all the relevant information. All of your data protection rights
            may apply, except the right to object. To be clear, you do have the right
            to withdraw your consent at any time.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal obligation</strong> - we have to collect or use your information
            so we can comply with the law. All of your data protection rights may
            apply, except the right to erasure, the right to object and the right
            to data portability.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> - we're collecting or using your
            information because it benefits you, our organisation or someone else,
            without causing an undue risk of harm to anyone. All of your data protection
            rights may apply, except the right to portability. Our legitimate interests
            are:
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Health information is collected to ensure the safety of people using
          our facilities, and ensure any necessary adjustments to can be made to
          accomodate their needs.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our lawful bases for collecting or using personal information for <strong
            >dealing with queries, complaints or claims</strong
          > are:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> - we have permission from you after we gave
            you all the relevant information. All of your data protection rights
            may apply, except the right to object. To be clear, you do have the right
            to withdraw your consent at any time.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>
        <a class="anchor" id="infofrom"></a>Where we get personal information
        from
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div>
        <ul>
          <li>Directly from you</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2><a class="anchor" id="retention"></a>How long we keep information</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div>
        <p>
          Personal information is kept for the duration of a person's
          membership, and for 36 months thereafter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2><a class="anchor" id="share"></a>Who we share information with</h2>

      <h3>Data processors</h3>

      <p><strong>Stripe</strong></p>
      <p>
        This data processor does the following activities for us: Payment
        processor
      </p>

      <p><strong>Google</strong></p>
      <p>
        This data processor does the following activities for us: Data storage
      </p>

      <p><strong>Retool</strong></p>
      <p>
        This data processor does the following activities for us: Data
        processing and storage
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2><a class="anchor" id="complain"></a>How to complain</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any concerns about our use of your personal data, you can
        make a complaint to us using the contact details at the top of this
        privacy notice.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you remain unhappy with how we’ve used your data after raising a
        complaint with us, you can also complain to the ICO.
      </p>
      <p>The ICO’s address:</p>
      <p>
        Information Commissioner’s Office<br />Wycliffe House<br />Water Lane<br
        />Wilmslow<br />Cheshire<br />SK9 5AF
      </p>
      <p>Helpline number: 0303 123 1113</p>
      <p>
        Website: <a
          data-udi="umb://document/ab9e48b8fcd3472bb798c3c4cfcb43d3"
          href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/"
          title="Make a complaint"
          >https://www.ico.org.uk<span>/make-a-complaint</span></a
        >
      </p>
      <h2><span>Last updated</span></h2>
      <p>10 January 2025</p>
      <p></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

